SaAHK *
SaAHK: see SaHowN. ― -b2- It is also said of one intoxicated [as meaning Recovering, or becoming free,
from his intoxication; or ceasing to be intoxicated: see 1]. (S, TA.)

SaraAriY~N *
SaraAriY~N A sailor: (S, M, K:) like SaArK: (S:) pl. SaraAriy~uwna: (S, M, K:) it has no broken pl.: (M:) or Sar~AriY~ should be [without tenween, imperfectly decl., and] mentioned in art. SrY; for it is pl. of Sur~aA='N, which is pl. of SaArK, which J has mentioned in art. SrY: AHát used to say that Sur~aA='N is a sing., like Hus~aAnN; but without sufficient authority: and J has regarded SaraAriY~ as a sing. in consequence of his finding it to have the same construction as a sing, in verses of Arabs;
whence he imagined the Y in it to be the relative Y, as is shown by his mentioning the word in this place. (IB.)

Suw~aAbapN *
Suw~aAbapN The choice, or best, class of a people;
(Fr, S, M, K;) as also Suy~aAbapN↓ (Fr, S, K) and Suy~aAbN↓. (K.) And qawomN Suy~aAbN↓ A choice, or an excellent, people. (S.) And Suy~aAbapN↓ signifies The choice, or best, of anything. (S.) [See also art. Syb.] ― -b2- Also, Suw~aAbapN, The collective body of a people; (M;) and so Suy~aAbapN↓. (Kr, M in art. Syb.)
